<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871207-0136 </DOCNO><HL> American Income LifeInsurance Stake of 8%Is Reported by Group</HL><DD> 12/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AINCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   A group including Boston-based FMR Corp. and Hamilton, Bermuda-based Fidelity International Ltd. said it holds an 8% stake in American Income Life Insurance Co.'s common shares outstanding.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the group said it holds 1,080,500 American Income Life common shares. Recent transactions include purchases of 45,000 American Income Life common shares from Sept. 4 to Nov. 12 for $9.88 to $14.13 a share. The group said it also sold 122,600 American Income Life shares from Oct. 6 to Oct. 21 for $9.95 to $13.75 a share.    According to the filing, the group purchased its American Income Life stock &quot;to acquire an equity interest in the company in pursuit of specified investment objectives.&quot; The group said it may buy more shares or sell some of its shares in the future, depending on market conditions and other factors. FMR and Fidelity International are investment managers that routinely buy and sell stakes in companies.    American Income Life is based in Waco, Texas. </TEXT></DOC>